  "id": "wildfire_visualization",
  "summary": "Cartographic wildfire visualization using Sentinel-2 SWIR imagery with multiple rendering styles.",
  "description": "Visualizes active wildfire occurrences from Sentinel-2 imagery using SWIR-based spectral thresholds blended into a base map that preserves soil, built-up areas, vegetation, and water bodies. Supports three rendering styles: a continuous fire intensity heatmap, and binary fire detection in red or yellow. Includes optional cloud avoidance logic to reduce false detections and burn-scar highlighting via the Normalized Burn Ratio (NBR) for post-fire impact assessment."
